1 PART III
2 SECTION 3. The sums hereinabove may be paid to the
3 respective persons, firms, corporations, or entities for the
4 satisfaction or settlement of the respectively identified cases,
5 and in several amounts hereinabove set forth or in lesser
6 amounts deemed appropriate, upon checks issued by the
7 comptroller; provided that departments shall obtain the approval
8 of the attorney general before payment of any claim may be made.
9 SECTION 4. Notwithstanding the sums hereinabove stated as
10 interest upon judgments against the State, payment of interest
11 shall be limited to the period from the date of the judgment, if
12 applicable, to thirty days after the effective date of this Act,
13 as provided in section 662-8, Hawaii Revised Statutes, for those
14 cases to which the statute applies.
15 SECTION 5. The appropriations made by this Act shall not
16 lapse at the end of the fiscal period for which the
17 appropriations are made; provided that all moneys from the
18 appropriations that are unexpended and unencumbered as of June
19 30, 2027, shall lapse as of that date.
20 SECTION 6. If any provision of this Act, or the
21 application thereof to any person or circumstance, is held
HB2250 SD2 LRB 26-1234-1.docx 7
